Pre-heat your oven to 200 degrees. Peel and cut the @onion{1}(peeled) in half and chop it into 1cm pieces. Peel your @red onion{1}(peeled), slice in half through the root and then thinly cut lengthways into half moon shapes.

> Make sure you keep the brown and red onions apart as it's important that we cook them separately in a bit!

Split the @pork and oregano sausage{500%g} lengthways and squeeze the meat into a #bowl{}, discarding the skin.

Heat 2 tbsp of @oil{2%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} and fry the (brown) onion for about ~{7%minutes} until lightly browned. Once cooked, add the onion to the sausage meat and stir together.

Lay out your sheet of @puff pastry sheet{1} on a flat surface and cut into two pieces widthways. One should be slightly bigger than the other. Place the smaller half on a lined #baking tray{} and brush the edges of the rectangle with some water. Place the sausage meat down the centre. Place the second pastry sheet over the top.

> This piece needs to be slightly bigger to fit over the filling.

Press the edges together with fingers or a #fork{} to seal the parcel. If you have any @?milk{}, brush a little over the top of the pastry to glaze it, if not don't worry! Make some small slits in the top of the pastry to allow the steam to escape and pop your sausage puff into the oven for ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Red Onion Marmalade ==

Heat 2 tbsp of @oil{2%tbsp} in the same pan you used in Step 3. Add the red onion and the @balsamic vinegar{2%tbsp}. Season with @salt{1/2%tsp} and a few good grinds of @black pepper{a few grinds}. Add 1/2 tbsp of @?sugar{1/2%tbsp}. Cover and simmer gently for ~{10-15%minutes} until softened. Once cooked, take the pan off the heat and set aside.

== Tomato and Watercress Salad ==

Cut your @cherry tomatoes{1}(cut in half) in half and slice your @cucumber{1}(sliced widthways) widthways. Mix the cherry tomatoes with the cucumber and @lambs lettuce and bulls blood mix{2%handfuls} in a bowl. Drizzle the @Seville orange & honey dressing{1.5%tbsp} over the salad.

== To Serve ==

Slice the sausage puff and serve with your red onion marmalade and salad.